Local government plays a critical role in drought management, particularly in the mobilisation of local resources. Local government should –
* act as conduit for information concerning drought disasters in the municipal area;
* act as an advisory body on drought disaster issues;
* incorporate early warning systems in its planning;
* make recommendations regarding assistance and initiate and facilitate efforts to
* establish disaster management centres within the municipal area; and
* prepare a municipal disaster management plan.

